ting such events for tourism bureaus, city administrators, elected officials, and the citizens they represent.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCity planningxUnited States. 0aCity planningzUnited States. 0aPolitical conventionsxPlanningxUnited States. 0aPolitical conventionsxSocial aspectsxUnited States. 0aPolitical conventionsxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aPolitical conventionszUnited StatesxPlanning. 4aPolitics and Law : American Politics. 4aPolitics and Law : Electoral Politics. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Parties. 4aPolitics and Law : Politics. 4aPublic Policy : Urban and Regional Planning. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Political Parties.2bisacsh1 aLeland, Suzanne M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSwindell, David, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846640840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438466408423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438466408/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles